headline: Chip Stocks Pop Despite Trump's Disdain for Key Industry Legislation
summary: Chipmakers are seeing a boost, despite Donald Trump's stance on legislation directing billions of dollars to them.  Stocks of companies that produce semiconductors were rising Wednesday after Trump was elected as president.  Shares of Qualcomm gained 3.8%, Micron Technology added 5.6% and Advanced Micro Devices rose 1.9%.
